<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 7:43AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Slippery and Snow Covered Roads this Morning...
Light snow will continue to fall across portions of North Central
through Southwest Montana, which will lead to snow covered and
slippery surfaces through the morning hours, especially over
mountain passes and on elevated surfaces like bridges and
overpasses. Roads will become mostly wet or slushy by the late
morning through early afternoon hours.
Travelers should be prepared for changing road conditions and
reduced visibility at times. Slow down, allow extra spacing
between vehicles, and extra time to reach your destination.</description>
